Sentencas: In this study, two new methods are proposed for manufacturing anode-supported tubular SOFCs (solid oxide fuel cells) with AFL (anode functional layer).
Titulo: A new method for manufacturing anode supported solid oxide fuel cells with AFL

Sentencas: The anode supports are manufactured via thermoplastic extrusion.
Titulo: A new method for manufacturing anode supported solid oxide fuel cells with AFL

Sentencas: PEG is used as a secondary binder in the anode tubes and it is selectively removed by water debinding and sweat debinding methods and an AFL layer is obtained with different microstructure and porosity.
Titulo: A new method for manufacturing anode supported solid oxide fuel cells with AFL

Sentencas: The Sweat debinding method is suggested as a new method for forming an alternative layer with a different microstructure than the main body of the anode support.
Titulo: A new method for manufacturing anode supported solid oxide fuel cells with AFL

Sentencas: Full cells are produced from the altered anode supports.
Titulo: A new method for manufacturing anode supported solid oxide fuel cells with AFL

Sentencas: The peak power densities of the cells are measured as 0.38 W/cm2 for Sweat Debound cells, while it is 0.29 W/cm2 for the Water Debound cells.
Titulo: A new method for manufacturing anode supported solid oxide fuel cells with AFL
